Ed Gaddy wrote:
&lt;blockquote TYPE=CITE&gt;
&lt;div class=Section1&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Arial&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#000080&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=-1&gt;I
am so very impressed with Quickscript that I am quite willing to accept
it as is. It is practically completely phonetic, very compact, without
diacrits, quick to go on paper, and, I think, attractive. Read really did
a fine job!&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Arial&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#000080&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=-1&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Arial&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#FF0000&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=-1&gt;I
agree with you Ed.&nbsp; As an example of QS&#39;s utility, I attended a meeting
of a non-profit corporation I am a member of over the weekend.&nbsp; Inadvertently,
I have become the defacto secretary because I can take notes quickly.&nbsp;
I took three pages of notes in QS and then later transcribed them onto
my laptop in roman.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Arial&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#FF0000&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=-1&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Arial&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#FF0000&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=-1&gt;Thus,
it is evident that although QS was not intended to function as a true shorthand,
it is so much more efficient than using roman to write English that it
can serve as an acceptable substitute for a shorthand.&nbsp; It was certainly
easier getting an accurate record of the meeting using QS than it would
have been using roman.&nbsp; Obviously, this would be a useful skill for
students taking notes in class to have at their fingertips, so to speak.&nbsp;
I believe we should try to stress these sorts of uses for QS to get people
thinking about how they can use QS in their lives.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Arial&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#FF0000&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=-1&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


